OL,6,FIan says: "They knew there was a
OL,7,Fproblem with it, it's been well
OL,8,Fdocumented in the infected blood
OL,9,Finquiry that they knew there was a
OL,10,Frisk but they carried on giving it to
OL,11,Fchildren."
OL,13,FIan faced a difficult childhood having
OL,14,Finherited haemophilia, a disorder
OL,15,Fwhere blood does not clot properly.
OL,17,FHe explains: "I missed a lot of
OL,18,Fschool, was teased a lot, called a
OL,19,F'bleeder'. People would hit me just to
OL,20,Fsee how quickly I bruised.
