OL,6,FIan's wife Angela Walden explains how
OL,7,Fthe condition affected their family
OL,8,Flife: "He couldn't help it at the time
OL,9,Fand we didn't know the medication was
OL,10,Fcausing the mood changes.
OL,12,F"Sometimes it was like walking on
OL,13,Feggshells. If the children were
OL,14,Fplaying up he just didn't have the
OL,15,Fpatience and he'd have to walk off and
OL,16,Fcalm down."
OL,18,FIn response, the British Government
OL,19,Fsays: "This was an appalling tragedy,
OL,20,Fand our thoughts remain with all those
OL,21,Fimpacted.
